title: Vienna, Marzen, Oktoberfest (Classic Beer Style #4)

Vienna, Marzen, Oktoberfest (Classic Beer Style #4)

By George and Laurie Fix

A product of the German brewing revolution, Oktoberfest is a sweet, malty lager and a satisfying brew. George Fix, outstanding brewer and author, and Laurie Fix, an active homebrewer and brewing competition judge, have written this well-researched profile of an enjoyable beer style to both drink and brew.

The Classic Beer Style Series from Brewers Publications examines individual world-class beer styles, covering origins, history, sensory profiles, brewing techniques and commercial examples.
